<p>1.The problem is group consecutive duplicates in a list to sublists. Example is  group([a,a,a,a,b,c,c,a,a,d,e,e,e,e]); [[a,a,a,a],[b],[c,c],[a,a],[d],[e,e,e,e]].   I am working on how to create a sublist.   Here is what I have so far:</p>  <pre><code>fun group([]) = nil | group(x::xs)= x::hd(xs)::group(xs) | group(x::y)= hd(x)::seven(tl(y)); </code></pre>  <p>also written in function</p>  <pre><code>fun g(L) = if L = [] then nil else if hd(L) = nth(2,L) then hd(L)::g(tl(L)) else [hd(L)]@g(tl(L)); </code></pre>  <p>Thank you for any help!</p>